HEADWORD: Tachyglossa
<hw>Tach`y*glos"sa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>tachy`s</grk> quick + <grk>glw^ssa</grk> tongue.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of monotremes which comprises the
spiny ant-eaters of Australia and New Guinea. See <xex>Illust.</xex>
under <er>Echidna</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

